@node "prefs" "Da Cool Installer Preferences"
@{b}Da Cool Installer Preferences@{ub}

  After massive request I`m finally able to present the Da Cool
  Installer Preferences editor (DCIP). Okay, what`s this now? Let me
  explain it with a simple example:  

  Imagine you`ve installed a game with DCI and after the start
  you see that the game has graphical errors. Now you need to
  emulate the ECS chipset. In previous versions you had to
  install the game completely new and select EmulateECS during
  the installation. Now you only need to start the Prefs
  Editor and select the EmulateECS option.

  That was only one example. There`re alot of things possible
  with the DCIP.

  DCIP comes with a full fontsensitive @{"MUI" link "MUI"} GUI.
  If you haven`t installed MUI yet, get it from Aminet (util/libs/MUI3.8usr.lha)
  or Internet: http://www.sasg.com. DCIP requires at least
  MUI3.8.
  
  Although DCIP features bubble help, I'll explain all buttons
  here:

  Path: If you`ve moved the game to an other
        place on your harddisk, you need to
        change the path here too. Otherwise
        the game won`t work.

  EmulateECS: Select this gadget if the game shall 
              run in ECS mode. This is most useful
              for old A500 games.

  Da Cool Booter: Set this to yes, if you wanna use Da
  		  Cool Booter for booting. You need a
  		  registered version of Da Cool Booter
  		  of course!

  Trackdisk.device: If Da Cool Installer has found the
  		    trackdisk.device in a game during the
  		    installation, you can switch the emulation
 		    on or off!

  Save: Saves the current settings. Exit and you can run
        the game with the new settings.

  About: Shows some information about the program.

  Exit: no comment

@endnode

