@node "wasmacht" "Introduction"
@{b}Introduction@{ub}

  dA cOOL iNSTALLER (DCI) installs nearly every standard Amiga
  game/demo on your harddisk.

  DCI has powerful features. If the game/demo is ECS, DCI degrades 
  the computer to ECS.
 
  DCI can install games/demos with more than one disk too.

  Even trackdisk.device is no problem for DCI. With my trackdisk.device
  emulation DOS games using trackdisk.device should run fine from HD.
 
  ...and the best of all. You don`t need any programming skills!

  Installing a game/demo is as easy as possible.
  See how @{"easy" link "install"} it is.

  Note: You cannot install games only with Da Cool Installer. You can
        install all what you want (Demos, Utilties, Applications...)

@endnode

