@node "System" "System Requirements"
@{b}System requirements@{ub}

  To use dA cOOL iNSTALLER you'll need at least an Amiga (oh, can`t I use
  it on PeeZee ?) with harddisk and OS2.04. I heard that Da Cool Installer
  runs on WinUAE too but you should use it on Amiga ;)

  dA cOOL iNSTALLER should be compatible up to A4000/060. It was successfully
  tested on A1200/030, A1200/040, A4000/040. I think there shouldn`t
  be any problems on higher machines. Let me know if there are.

  dA cOOL iNSTALLER requires also the reqtools.library (© by Niço François)
  in libs:. I`ve stored it in the dA cOOL iNSTALLER`s dir in libs/. Too
  bad that Niço quit the scene :-(

  For the recommended installation of dA cOOL iNSTALLER you'll need the tool
  NewInstaller. Get it on Aminet (util/wb/NewInstaller.lha) or on our homepage
  http://www.airsoftsoftwair.de/.

  Additionally you must have the Workbench installed on your harddisk and
  boot with it.

@endnode

@node "install" "Installing things"
@{b}Installing a game/demo/program/whatever@{ub}

  It`s so easy.......

  I`ll explain it to you in three simple steps:

  1) Start dA cOOL iNSTALLER
  2) Select the destination path
  3) Insert a game or demo disk in DF0:

  THAT WAS IT! ALL IS DONE! Now start the game/demo and @{"register" link "register"}.


  If you're a registered user, you can select some more options
  during the installation procedure:

  1) Select game format: DOS:  The most used format on Amiga! The most games,
                               demos, programs use it. Da Cool Installer`s
                               DOS support is great. It works for nearly all
                               games!

                         DMS:  This is a packed disk format. The unpacked
 			       DMS disk needs to be in DOS format. NDOS isn`t
			       supported in this case yet!

  2) Select diskdrive to use: DF0: This is the standard Amiga internal inbuild
				   floppydrive! Select this if you haven`t any
				   external drives.

 			      DF1: This is an external drive.

 			      DF2: This is an external drive too.


  3) Do you wanna use EmulateTrackdisk.device Option? Yes: Select this if you`re
							   sure that the game
							   uses trackdisk.device.
							   Da Cool Installer checks
							   all files then and tries
							   to find files which use
 							   trackdisk.device. If it
							   finds one you can let
							   it patch. If you`re not
							   sure if the game uses
							   trackdisk.device you can
							   of course let DCI check
							   if it finds one.

						       No: Don`t use the option. 

  4) Do you wanna use EmulateECS Option? Yes: Select this if the game you wanna
					      install is an old A500 game and has
					      problems with running on higher
					      machines. Never use it with AGA
					      games!!

     					 No:  Don`t use this option.

  5) Do you wanna use Da Cool Booter for booting? Yes: Select this if the game needs
						       the full 2MB Chip RAM or if it
						       doesn`t like Setpatch. Note: You
                                                       need Da Cool Booter for this
                                                       option. You can get Da Cool Booter
                                                       from Aminet.

   						  No:  Don`t use this option.

  6) Shall I create a .DCI file for you? Yes: This creates a .DCI file for the currently
					      installed game. See @{"here" link "dci"} for more
					      information about .DCI files.

					 No:  Don`t create a .DCI file.
 

@endnode

@node "dci" "The .DCI install files"
@{b}The DCI install files@{ub}

  From Version 1.5 on Da Cool Installer can create .DCI files for you.
  
  Let me explain what a .DCI file is good for....For example you just
  installed Crazy Cars III successfully with Da Cool Installer and then
  select the option that Da Cool Installer creates a .DCI file for you.

  Now you have the .DCI for example in RAM:. If you doubleclick it now
  you can install Crazy Cars III again - but much easier - you have
  only to insert the disks and select the destination. No more options
  will appear!
  
  You can create .DCI files for your favourite games and spread them
  around (Aminet etc...). Some example files are supplied in the Demos/
  directory!  
  
@endnode
   
@node "option" "Starting a game/demo"
@{b}Starting an installed game@{ub}

  Simply doubleclick the icon.

  If the game doesn`t start, there`re several possibilities why,

  1) the game/demo uses a trackdisk loader, then use Trackdisk.device emulation
     (only registered version)
  2) the game/demo must be degraded (only @{"registered" link "register"} version
  3) the game/demo uses a non-standard loader, these can`t be installed generally
  4) other error !?
  
@endnode

